overview:
Moshe Katzenelson is an experienced seed-stage investor with hands-on experience in engineering, project management, international sales and strategic planning. Before heading Technion Seed, Moshe Katzenelson spent over seven years with Israeli venture capital funds. He managed investments at StageOne Ventures and at LabOne Innovations, the fundâ€™s start-up incubator.

Moshe Katzenelson began his career in the Israeli Air Force R&D unit and then held marketing and sales positions with ECI Telecom. He also filled key marketing and strategic planning positions at Pelephone, Israel’s first cellular carrier.
